e is now most common in Banffshire and Orkney."]}]},{"name":"Lawrence","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of   Laurence .  This is the usual spelling of the surname, and is now becoming increasingly common as a given name, especially in North America."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":13,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":86,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Lawrence Fleet Knight was born in 1369, in Fleet, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Sir Lawrence Fleet, was 41 and his mother, Lady Lawrence Fleet, was 38. He married Lady Lawrence Fleet in 1394, in Fleet, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in Wisbech, Cambridgeshire, England."},"et":{"1369–":"1369–Surnud","1356–1421":"1356–1421","1369–Male":"1369–Surnud","1374–Female":"1374–Surnud","1395–Female":"1395–Surnud","1328–Male":"1328–Surnud","1331–Female":"1331–Surnud","1369":"1369","1455":"1455","1356":"1356","1421":"1421","1331":"1331